codex
A key challenge to the framing: the `m_graphicsData` slot for `ShaderImplementationPassPixelShaderProgram` is only directly assigned in three places in `ShaderImplementation.cpp`: constructor, reload unload-to-null, reload recreate. The destructor deletes the data but does not set `m_graphicsData = 0`, which is harmless only if no stale `Program*` remains reachable. That makes refcount/map lifetime the next place to scrutinize.
