codex
Another important correction: D3D11’s lost/restored callback implementation only records callbacks and never invokes them; PPEM calls `deviceRestored()` directly during `enable()`. So a D3D9-style device-lost remove/restore is unlikely to be the mechanism here unless some higher-level code explicitly disables/re-enables PPEM or releases the shader/template. The stronger suspect is a shared `Program*` refcount/lifetime bug or a use-after-free of the whole `ShaderImplementationPassPixelShaderProgram` object.
