The dump actually points at a stronger, different root: `0x21250030` is the `ShaderImplementationPassPixelShaderProgram::m_graphicsData` slot, so `m_program` itself is plausibly the freed/reused object. A valid `Program` object has `m_graphicsData` at that offset; if its storage was reused for `PersistentCrcString` list nodes, then `construct()` is walking a dangling engine `m_program`, not a live program with a bad D3D11 subobject.
