The refcount chain looks normal at a glance: `ShaderImplementationPassPixelShader` owns a fetched `Program*` and releases it in its destructor. The failure mode that fits the dump is therefore not “PS-data freed while program stays live”; it is “some pass/static shader is holding a stale `ShaderImplementation`/`Pass`/`PixelShader` graph after the effect/implementation was released,” or corruption of that graph. I’m pulling the static-template/effect ownership lines to see if D3D11 cached pointers outlive that graph.
