There is also a D3D11-specific amplifier in the attempted fix: storing `m_passPSSlot = &program->m_graphicsData` is only safe if `program` is stable. Your dump says that address itself lives inside reused storage. Even if D3D9 reads live fields, it reads through the pass graph at apply time; D3D11’s slot-address cache can preserve a dangling interior pointer after a program/pass release.
