One more framing issue: if `StaticShader` did not keep its template/effect alive, D3D9 would be broken too. The code likely relies on `Shader` retaining the template; I’m not going to claim template release as root without dump evidence. The actionable distinction is narrower: validate whether the *program object address* is live, not only whether the D3D11 wrapper at `m_graphicsData` has sane vectors.
